<subSubSection id="A1CD68FB63188BF1368EB0BE77A49444" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="13BFADC82D786292EA6C3F12063ACFFC" pageNumber="50">
The killifish genus 
<taxonomicName id="F2DCA03F2646FC36B5292EA1257105B4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus Poey</taxonomicName>
constitutes the most speciose and geographically widespread assemblage of aplocheiloid fishes. A great diversity in species of 
<taxonomicName id="FEC31D8CB5CB065C2F853774F52E7973" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
has long been known from Central America and the northern part of South America, including river basins draining the Guyana Shield and the western portion of the Rio Amazonas basin (Costa, 2003, 2006). However, a rich diversity of species has only recently been reported for the central part of South America, including southern tributaries of the rio Amazonas (Tocantins, Araguaia, Xingu, and 
<normalizedToken id="DF6C29C038CE53AD3C2F014D241A82A0" originalValue="Tapajós">Tapajos</normalizedToken>
) and the rio 
<normalizedToken id="64396E08E69A3D0372C71C1E8EB3896C" originalValue="Paraná-Paraguay-">Parana-Paraguay-Uruguay</normalizedToken>
basin (Costa, 1995a, 2005). 
<taxonomicName id="E72BF1A4795EA5828F7E47C2094983CF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
is still a poorly diagnosed genus, but it contains well-corroborated monophyletic units. This is the case for an assemblage formerly known as the 
<taxonomicName id="253646AAF9F96AAE58696403D5D4DAFC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:089B99CF-4A7B-4D32-9C0C-17750DE26936" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus punctatus Boulenger 1895:3" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">Rivulus punctatus species group</taxonomicName>
(Costa, 1995a), now considered to comprise the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1CC3A38550294987A968A1DD86B4E263" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Melanorivulus">Melanorivulus</taxonomicName>
(Costa, 2006), a well supported clade endemic to central South America. This subgenus comprises 18 species: 
<taxonomicName id="C34CA23C781881A797BCCF034F57492F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:673744D8-BF31-4FC5-98F4-B64275067211" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus apiamici Costa 1989:527" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apiamici">Rivulus apiamici Costa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A3219E807E52BF68DE3AD4B003BC2F4D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4045A1A6-88DA-4A5C-917A-2BE1BB7F3395" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus cyanopterus Costa 2005:73" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyanopterus">R. cyanopterus Costa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B251EB75A320160A0329C2B647E0C6F6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1FF92E36-F75B-4D13-9AAE-4C3B9C011783" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus dapazi Costa 2005:71" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dapazi">R. dapazi Costa</taxonomicName>
